+## Review invariants after correction
+
+1. Critical scientific and security rules live in deterministic code, not prompt text or import side effects.
+2. Compatibility modules cannot alter runtime behavior.
+3. `GO` means the supplied contract passed the current deterministic proposal gates; it does not mean publication-ready science.
+4. Synthetic, mixed/unverified, and real-verified evidence are distinct machine-readable states.
+5. A real-verified proposal can advance to controlled experimentation only after the deterministic gates pass.
+6. Scientific release remains false until observed results have immutable evidence and domain-expert review is complete.
+7. Every comparison arm uses the same data, preprocessing, tuning budget, metrics, seeds, uncertainty reporting, resource accounting, and stopping criteria.
+8. Baseline and borrowed modules require stable, claim-bearing provenance and acceptable reuse terms.
+9. Unknown module references, empty proposed modules, contaminated baselines, fabricated observed results, and non-finite metrics fail closed.
+10. Diagnostics report observed database state and do not expose prompts, credentials, request bodies, or idempotency keys.
